domestic product report  statement of secretary john w snow on the  third quarter gross domestic product report  page content     from the office of public affairs js  today�s report on real gdp in the third quarter shows that the president�s economic policies are having a positive impact on the economy the jobs and growth act has put more money in the pockets of american families and helped businesses to make new investments we are seeing signs of economic recovery the value of us stock markets has increased  trillion since the beginning of this year disposable personal income is up  percent at an annual rate in  and the us homeownership rate was  percent in the third quarter � its highest level ever the gdp report is certainly very encouraging news for our economy but we still have more work to do to ensure that every american who wants a job can find a job i look forward to working with the president and congress to implement additional economic initiatives that will keep the us economy firmly on the road to recovery      the current browser does not support web pages that contain the iframe element to use this web part you must use a browser that supports this element such as internet explorer  or later treasury facts the treasury is the oldest departmental building in washington and at the time of its completion it was one of the largest office buildings in the world featured video secretary jack lews currency announcement at the national archives treasury secretary jacob j lew delivered remarks on currency redesign at the national archives thursday june   secretary lews remarks expanded on his decision to redesign the  note social media privacy featured photo see more photos social media privacy   untitled  initiatives financial stability housing finance reform making home affordable recovery us china strategic and economic dialogue wall street reform languages العربية s español 한국어 tagalog tiếngviệt bureaus the alcohol and tobacco tax and trade bureau bureau 